		"description": "<p>You learn the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.b87rq9617y6ysv5l]{Bothersome Buzzing} cantrip. Additionally, when you or one of your allies within 30 feet of you is hit with a melee weapon attack, you may use your reaction to vigorously vibrate your wings, creating a loud buzzing or whirring sound that can drive the enemy to distraction. You or the triggering ally may immediately roll 1d4 and add the result to your/their AC, potentially causing the enemy to miss. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest.</p>",
